Title : John Berkeley (1352–1428)
Text : {{short description|English politician}}
{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2016}}
{{Use British English|date=November 2016}}
'''Sir John Berkeley''' (21 January 1352–5 March 1428)<ref name="parliament">{{cite web|url=http://www.historyofparliamentonline.org/volume/1386-1421/member/berkeley-sir-john-i-1352-1428|title=BERKELEY, Sir John I (1352-1428), of Beverstone castle, Glos. - History of Parliament Online|website=www.historyofparliamentonline.org}}</ref>, of [[Beverston Castle]], [[Gloucestershire]] was an English politician. He was the son of [[Thomas de Berkeley, 3rd Baron Berkeley]] of [[Berkeley Castle]] and Katherine Clivedon. He was knighted before 1383.

He was appointed [[High Sheriff of Somerset]] and [[High Sheriff of Dorset|Dorset]] for 1390–91 and 1394–95, [[High Sheriff of Gloucestershire]] for 1392–93, 1397–98 and 1414–15, [[High Sheriff of Hampshire]] for 1402–03 and 1406–07, and [[High Sheriff of Wiltshire]] for 1410–11.

He was a [[Member of Parliament|Member]] (MP) of the [[Parliament of England]] for [[Gloucestershire (UK Parliament constituency)|Gloucestershire]] in February 1388, September 1388 and January 1397, for [[Somerset (UK Parliament constituency)|Somerset]] in November 1390 and 1394, for [[Wiltshire (UK Parliament constituency)|Wiltshire]] in 1402 and [[Hampshire (UK Parliament constituency)|Hampshire]] in 1406.<ref name="parliament"></ref>
He married 3 times, but only had issue by his second wife, Elizabeth Betteshorne.<ref name="parliament"></ref> John and Elizabeth had 14 sons and 3 daughters.<ref name="parliament"></ref> 
* Eleanor Berkeley, married [[John FitzAlan, 13th Earl of Arundel]] and had issue.<ref name="parliament"></ref> She married secondly to Sir Richard Poynings, son of Robert Poynings, 4th Baron Poynings.<ref name="parliament"></ref> Their daughter, Eleanor, married [[Henry Percy, 3rd Earl of Northumberland]]. She married thirdly to [[Walter Hungerford, 1st Baron Hungerford]].<ref name="parliament"></ref>
* Sir Maurice de Berkeley, married Lora FitzHugh.<ref name="parliament"></ref>
* Elizabeth de Berkeley, married firstly to [[Edward Charleton, 5th Baron Cherleton|Sir Edward Charleton, Baron Charleton of Powis]] by whom she had issue.<ref name="parliament"></ref> Secondly, she married [[John Sutton, 1st Baron Dudley|John Sutton, Baron Dudley]] by whom she had issue.<ref name="parliament"></ref>
* Joan de Berkeley, married to Sir Thomas Stawell.<ref name="parliament"></ref>

